  #Above-ground biomass data for the Copper Mountain Mine study site
CMM.Bio <- mx_biomass_2022 %>%filter(Site == "CMM")
  #Above-ground biomass data for the Kamloops Wastewater Treatment study site
KAM.Bio <- mx_biomass_2022 %>%filter(Site == "KAM")  
  #Plant canopy coverage data for the Copper Mountain Mine study site in 2021 August

  #Plant canopy coverage data for the Copper Mountain Mine study site in 2022 August
CMM.Cov.2 <- mx_coverage_2021_2022 %>%filter(Site == "CMM",Year==2022)

And since the sowing treatment was tested on the second year, so the difference between two sowing groups in 2021 seems not have a big difference. Then for 2022, maybe "Reseed" plots had higher coverage in "CMM". And the coverage of "KAM" decreased in second year for both treatments.

Model Fit

  #Model fit for CMM Biomass 
  #No random effect structure
CMM.Bio.mod1 <- gls(log.mass ~ Sow_Treatment*Soil_Treatment, data = CMM.Bio, method = "REML")
  #Random Intercept
CMM.Bio.mod2 <- lme(log.mass ~ Sow_Treatment*Soil_Treatment, random = ~ 1|Block, data = CMM.Bio, method = "REML")
  #Random Intercept and Slope
CMM.Bio.mod3 <- lme(log.mass ~ Sow_Treatment*Soil_Treatment, random = ~ Sow_Treatment|Block, data = CMM.Bio, method = "REML")
#CMM.Bio.mod4 <- lme(log.mass ~ Sow_Treatment*Soil_Treatment, random = ~ Soil_Treatment|Block, data = CMM.Bio, method = "ML")
#[Error in lme.formula(log.mass ~ Sow_Treatment * Soil_Treatment, random = ~Soil_Treatment | : nlminb problem, convergence error code = 1 
#message = iteration limit reached without convergence (10)] So, I did not choose the slope of soil treatments

  #CMM Diversity
library(spaa)
CMM.Cov$abundance<-round(CMM.Cov$Mean_Coverage_Percentage,digits = 0)
CMM.Cov$plotname<-paste(CMM.Cov$Block,CMM.Cov$Plot,sep = "-")
CMM.Cov2<-transmute(CMM.Cov,plotname,Sowing_Treatment, Soil_Treatment,Species,abundance)
names(CMM.Cov2)[4]<-"species"
  #delete data of bareground, only require data of plants
CMM.Cov2<-subset(CMM.Cov2, species != 'Bare_Ground')
CMM.abundance<-aggregate(CMM.Cov2$abundance,by=list(type=CMM.Cov2$Soil_Treatment,CMM.Cov2$Sowing_Treatment,CMM.Cov2$species),sum)
names(CMM.abundance)[1]<-"Soil_Treatment"
names(CMM.abundance)[2]<-"Sowing_Treatment"
names(CMM.abundance)[3]<-"species"
names(CMM.abundance)[4]<-"abundance"
CMM.abundance$plotname<-paste(CMM.abundance$Soil_Treatment,CMM.abundance$Sowing_Treatment,sep = "_")
CMM.abundance2<-CMM.abundance %>% mutate(Soil_Treatment=NULL,Sowing_Treatment=NULL)
library(reshape2)
CMM.abundance.nonInteger<- acast(CMM.abundance2, formula = plotname ~ species, value.var = "abundance",fill = 0)
library(vegan)
## 载入需要的程辑包：permute
## 载入需要的程辑包：lattice
## This is vegan 2.6-4
Shannon_index<-diversity(CMM.abundance.nonInteger,index = "shannon")
Simpson_index<-diversity(CMM.abundance.nonInteger,index = "simpson")
Inverse.Simpson<-diversity(CMM.abundance.nonInteger,index = "invsimpson")
Richness<-specnumber(CMM.abundance.nonInteger)
Pielou<-Shannon_index/log(Richness)
CMM.Diversity<-as.data.frame(cbind(Shannon_index,Simpson_index,Inverse.Simpson,Richness,Pielou))
CMM.Diversity$Soil_Treatment<-c("Control","Control","High","High","Low","Low","Medium","Medium")
CMM.Diversity$Sow_Treatment<-c("Reseed","Seed_Once","Reseed","Seed_Once","Reseed","Seed_Once","Reseed","Seed_Once")
CMM.Diversity[is.na(CMM.Diversity)] <- 0
View(CMM.Diversity)
#Export table
#write.table(CMM.Diversity,file="CMM_Diversity.April.csv",sep=",",row.names = TRUE)
CMM.Diversity.aov1<-aov(data = CMM.Diversity,Shannon_index~Sow_Treatment)
TukeyHSD(CMM.Diversity.aov1)
##   Tukey multiple comparisons of means
##     95% family-wise confidence level
## 
## Fit: aov(formula = Shannon_index ~ Sow_Treatment, data = CMM.Diversity)
## 
## $Sow_Treatment
##                         diff       lwr       upr     p adj
## Seed_Once-Reseed -0.09492537 -1.002649 0.8127981 0.8065854
  #p value is 0.807 (<0.05)
CMM.Diversity.aov2<-aov(data = CMM.Diversity,Shannon_index~Soil_Treatment)
TukeyHSD(CMM.Diversity.aov2)

  #KAM Diversity
KAM.Cov$abundance<-round(KAM.Cov$Mean_Coverage_Percentage,digits = 0)
KAM.Cov$plotname<-paste(KAM.Cov$Block,KAM.Cov$Plot,sep = "-")
KAM.Cov2<-transmute(KAM.Cov,plotname,Sowing_Treatment, Soil_Treatment,Species,abundance)
names(KAM.Cov2)[4]<-"species"
KAM.Cov2<-subset(KAM.Cov2, species != 'Bare_Ground')
KAM.Cov3<-transmute(KAM.Cov2,plotname, Sowing_Treatment, Soil_Treatment)
KAM.Cov4<-unique(KAM.Cov3)
KAM.Cov4<-KAM.Cov4[order(KAM.Cov4$plotname),]
KAM.abundance.nonInteger<- acast(KAM.Cov2, formula = plotname ~ species, value.var = "abundance",fill = 0)
Shannon_index<-diversity(KAM.abundance.nonInteger,index = "shannon")
Simpson_index<-diversity(KAM.abundance.nonInteger,index = "simpson")
Inverse.Simpson<-diversity(KAM.abundance.nonInteger,index = "invsimpson")
Richness<-specnumber(KAM.abundance.nonInteger)
Pielou<-Shannon_index/log(Richness)
KAM.Diversity<-as.data.frame(cbind(Shannon_index,Simpson_index,Inverse.Simpson,Richness,Pielou))
KAM.Diversity$Soil_Treatment<-KAM.Cov4$Soil_Treatment
KAM.Diversity$Sow_Treatment<-KAM.Cov4$Sowing_Treatment
KAM.Diversity[is.na(KAM.Diversity)] <- 0
View(KAM.Diversity)
#write.table(CMM.Diversity,file="KAM_Diversity.csv",sep=",",row.names = TRUE)
KAM.Diversity.aov1<-aov(data = KAM.Diversity,Shannon_index~Sow_Treatment)
TukeyHSD(KAM.Diversity.aov1)
